...and any derision from the customer certainly would not help. 

A week later I received a coupon for an additional 5 days' car rental in the mail with a letter. 

20 years later - my only memory is the exemplary service.  Thanks again.

We enjoyed the car for a week.   When I returned the vehicle at the airport the same manager asked, "why were you so nice? "   

I replied he had obviously been working hard and doing everything possible in a difficult situation on xmas eve...

John drove me to Sydney - I bought him dinner and provided appropriate gratuity.  He had saved me gas and the stress of driving. 

Next day - John, along with 2 colleagues appeared at the door with a brand new Volvo AWD wagon.  Upgrade - thanks.

Desk person (Manager?) says - "but we have a plan..."

"This is John and he will drive you anywhere you need to go in his personal vehicle.." 

I said, "really, I am going to Sydney (400kms)"

"No problem."
